    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This section introduces the
importance of goal setting&amp;nbsp; and how you can create an environment where
learners feel safe to set goals. This module will further identify how you can
use the tangible strategies in the Universal Design for Learning (UDL)
framework to design instructional goals and&amp;nbsp;help your students learn how
to set and accomplish their own goals &lt;a href="$@PAGEVIEWBYID*9628@$&amp;amp;forceview=1" target="_blank"&gt;(CAST, 2018)&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider-wave-1%20%282%29.png" alt="" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
